<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
    <head>
        <title>Star City Recycling</title>
        <link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="/css/bootstrap.css" media="all">
        <link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="/css/main.css" media="all">
        <script type="text/javascript" src="/js/jquery-1.9.0-min.js"></script>
        <script type="text/javascript" src="/js/jquery.labelify.js"></script>
    </head>
    <body>
        <div id="top">
            <div id="top_logo"></div>
        </div>
        <div id="main">
            <div class="container">
                <h1 id="main_title">
                    Bringing Curbside Recycling To Roanoke County
                </h1>
                <div id="main_bin"></div>
                <div id="main_contents">
                    <h3>
                        Save The Environment And Your Time!
                    </h3>
                    <ul>
                        <li>
                                No Sorting Required!
                        </li>
                        <li>
                                Easy Curbside Pickup Every Week
                        </li>
                        <li>
                                Only 66 cents a day!
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                    <a href="#get_started" id="get_started_btn"></a>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div id="how_it_works">
            <div class="container">
                <div id="how_it_works_tag">
                    <h3>How It Works</h3>
                </div>
                <div class="row">
                    <div class="span4">
                        <div class="how-it-works-box" style="margin-left: 30px;">
                            <img class="how-it-works-icon" src="/images/step_1_img.jpg" alt="">
                            <span class="step-number">
                                <h1>1</h1>
                            </span>
                            <h4>
                                Receive your recycle bin
                            </h4>
                            <p>
                                Only one bin is needed for all your recyclables.  You can use your own bin or purchase one from us ($15).
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="span4">
                        <div class="how-it-works-box">
                            <img class="how-it-works-icon" src="/images/step_2_img.jpg" alt="">
                            <span class="step-number">
                                <h1>2</h1>
                            </span>
                            <h4>
                                Put recyclables in your bin
                            </h4>
                            <p>
                                Place your paper, plastic, metal cans, and glass in your bin.  Not sure what recycle see What you Can and cannot Recycle
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="span4">
                        <div class="how-it-works-box">
                            <img class="how-it-works-icon" src="/images/step_3_img.jpg" alt="">
                            <span class="step-number">
                                <h1>3</h1>
                            </span>
                            <h4>
                                Place your bin on the curb
                            </h4>
                            <p>
                                No need to sort anything.  We will pickup your recyclables every week and sort them for you!
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                </div>
                <div class="inner-container" style="margin-top: 50px;">
                    <div class="page-section">
                        <h2>What you can and cannot recycle</h2>
                    </div>
                    <table id="can_cannot_recycle">
                        <tr>
                            <th>
                            </th>
                            <th class="can-recycle">
                                Can Recycle
                            </th>
                            <th class="cannot-recycle">
                                Cannot Recycle
                            </th>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <td class="category">
                                Paper
                            </td>
                            <td class="can-recycle">
                                Paper bags, Newspaper, Cardboard, Office paper, Magazines, Phone books, Paper gift wrap
                            </td>
                            <td class="cannot-recycle">
                                Milk Cartons, Paper or cardboard with plastic coating, Any type of paper with food waste, such as paper towels and pizza boxes.
                            </td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <td class="category">
                                Plastic
                            </td>
                            <td class="can-recycle">
                                Roanoke County accept plastics #1-#7.  The number will be found on the container inside the recycling symbol. If there is not a number, please don't recycle.
                            </td>
                            <td class="cannot-recycle">
                                Store-bought garbage bags, Bubble wrap, plastic packaging wrap
                            </td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <td class="category">
                                Metal Cans
                            </td>
                            <td class="can-recycle">
	                            Drink cans, Aluminum cans, Tin cans, Metal caps and tops
                            </td>
                            <td class="cannot-recycle">
                                Scrap metal, Car parts, Wire fencing, Compact Fluorescent Light Bulbs
                            </td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <td class="category">
                                Glass
                            </td>
                            <td class="can-recycle">
	                            All types of glass
                            </td>
                            <td class="cannot-recycle">
                                Broken glass
                            </td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <td>
                            </td>
                            <td class="can-recycle can-recycle-bottom"></td>
                            <td class="cannot-recycle cannot-recycle-bottom"></td>
                        </tr>
                    </table>
                    <div class="recycle-table-details">
                        <p>
                            Your recycling bin should have all dry material with no liquids or food waste present.  Break down your boxes in order to make room in the bin
                        </p>

                        <p>
                            If you are wondering if a material is recyclable or not, it may be easier to look at what NOT to recycle.  When in doubt, leave it out!

                        </p>

                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div id="get_started">
            <div class="container">
                <div class="inner-container">
                    <div class="faq-col">
                        <h2>Getting Started</h2>
                        <h4 class="faq-question">
                            How much does it costs?
                        </h4>
                        <p class="faq-answer">
                            The cost for our curbside pickup service is $20 per month.
                        </p>
                        <h4 class="faq-question">
                            Don't have a recycling bin?
                        </h4>
                        <p class="faq-answer">
                            We can supply a 32-gallon bin for $15 or you may use your own bin.
                        </p>
                        <h4 class="faq-question">
                            Am I eligible for the service?
                        </h4>
                        <p class="faq-answer">
                            Currently we are only offering pickup service in certain areas in the 24018 zip code.  If you'd like to know if your eligible please fill the form out and include your address.
                        </p>
                        <h4 class="faq-question">
                            How do I pay?
                        </h4>

                        <p class="faq-answer">
                            Checks, credit cards, and cash are all acceptable forms of payment.  Checks need to made out to Star City Recycling.
                        </p>

                        <p class="faq-answer">
                            You can either pay in person or mail checks to: <br>
                            P.O. Box 20312 Roanoke, VA 24018
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="form-col">
                        <p class="get-started-form-instructions">
                            To get started with Star City Recycling or if you have any questions, fill our the information below and we will contact you to help you get ready for the next pickup.
                        </p>

                        <form id="get_started_form">
                            <input type="text" name="name" id="get_started_name" title="name">
                            <input type="text" name="email" id="get_started_email" title="email">
                            <input type="text" name="phone" id="get_started_phone" title="phone number (optional)">
                            <textarea name="message" id="get_started_message" cols="30" rows="5" title="message"></textarea>

                            <div class="submit-wrapper">
                                <!--<input type="submit" value="Send Message" class="btn get-started-submit-btn" />-->
                                This feature is coming soon.  Please contact us vis Email or Phone below.
                                <div class="cl">&nbsp;</div>
                            </div>
                        </form>
                        <hr>
                        <p class="other-contact-methods">
                            Or you may also call or email to set up your service or if you have any questions
                        </p>

                        <div class="contact-info">
                            <a class="email-link" href="mailto:starcityrecycling@gmail.com">starcityrecycling@gmail.com</a>
                            <span class="phone-number">(540) 798-9107</span>
                            <div class="cl">&nbsp;</div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="cl">&nbsp;</div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div id="about_us">
            <div class="container">
                <div class="inner-container">
                    <div>
                        <div class="mission-col">
                            <h1>Our Mission</h1>
                            <ul class="mission-points">
                                <li>
                                    Roanoke County does not offer a curbside recycling service, making recycling an inconvenience
                                </li>
                                <li>
                                    So it is no surprise that our recycling rates are way behind our neighboring cities. Just take a look at the graph below.
                                </li>
                                <li>
                                    Star City Recycling offers the convenient curbside service we need to make recycling simple in the Roanoke County!
                                </li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>
                        <div class="info-col">
                            <div class="well">
                            <p>
                                My name is Edward Arsura and I have lived in Roanoke County for 15 years.  I have always had an interest in environment issues. In 2011 I graduated from James Madison University with a degree in Biology. After graduation I moved to Portland, Oregon for a year. Recycling is a huge part of their community and this is where I discovered how easy and beneficial recycling is. I was amazed to found out that trash was picked up once every TWO weeks due the amount of recyclable material we actually produce. This was when I realized I had to make recycling easier for the Roanoke County and so I started Star City Recycling upon my return to Roanoke.
                            </p>

                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

            </div>
        </div>
        <div id="footer" style="height: 400px; width: 100%">

        </div>

        <script type="text/javascript">
            $(document).ready(function(){
              $(":text, textarea").labelify({labelledClass: "labelOn"});
            });
        </script>
    </body>
</html>